content.description:
*Copied description from climbing.com**

  "THE CLASSIC HARD BACKBONE CLIMB. Climb the thin crack to a dihedral (about 45 ft up). Stem the dihedral to a ledge. Top out on a hard hanging offwidth. (~70 feet)" 

  50' to the left of Devil's Hideaway (the one with the obvious roof).
content.protection: Trees near the top you can sling for anchors.

content.description: 25 feet right of Monster Crack. Climb the hand crack up to the large roof. Go left through the roof and the hold all but disapear.
content.protection: Set top rope anchors from two trees directly above the route
content.location: Follow The Backbone Trail down to the west side and loop back to the bend in the river. There are several steep short cuts for a more adventurous trip to the bottom.

content.description: The West side of the backbone has the highest concentration of quality routes in the park.  It is also has the tallest climbs.  Access from pull out at base.
